    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "dec_body",
      "x": 433,
      "y": 1090,
      "width": 664,
      "height": 300,
      "strokeColor": "#8888aa",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 3,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 2,
      "index": "b2",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775830000000,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "MENTAL MODEL: Physical ledger book / 3-ring binder — not a VS Code clone.\nThe layout resembles an IDE workbench because both solve the same problem.\n\nGENERAL LEDGER IS MASTER. All views are projections/filters of it.\n- Selecting an account = focuses that slice of the GL. Not a separate data store.\n- Period selector = global temporal context. All views subscribe to currentPeriod.\n- Text search = further filter, but changes view semantics (see balance modes below).\n\nTABS = account dividers in the binder. Each tab is one account register.\n\nCOA SIDEBAR = persistent across all activities (like Obsidian, unlike VS Code).\nQuick action buttons are contextual to what is selected in the tree.\n\nPERIOD SELECTOR = application-level global context, not a per-view filter.\nSame interaction pattern as command palette. Natural language input supported.\nAffects: ledger, reports, scheduled txns, import/export — all views interpret it.\n\nBALANCE COLUMN — two modes:\n  Complete slice (account + period, no text search):\n    → Running balance. Pre-compute opening balance as of period start.\n  Filtered slice (text search active):\n    → Drop running balance. Show per-row amounts + filtered subtotal.\n  Status bar signals the mode.\n\nBOTTOM PANEL = front pocket of the binder. Global appliance only.\n  Import/export flows, reconciliation queue, scheduled transaction log.\n  Not a developer terminal for end users.\n\nSTATUS BAR = Obsidian-style. Floats near edges, only as wide as content.\n  API online/offline, balance, last reconcile date. Nothing useless in the middle.\n\nSCHEDULED TRANSACTIONS + BUDGETING = activity bar sections (separate binder sections).",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "MENTAL MODEL: Physical ledger book / 3-ring binder — not a VS Code clone.\nThe layout resembles an IDE workbench because both solve the same problem.\n\nGENERAL LEDGER IS MASTER. All views are projections/filters of it.\n- Selecting an account = focuses that slice of the GL. Not a separate data store.\n- Period selector = global temporal context. All views subscribe to currentPeriod.\n- Text search = further filter, but changes view semantics (see balance modes below).\n\nTABS = account dividers in the binder. Each tab is one account register.\n\nCOA SIDEBAR = persistent across all activities (like Obsidian, unlike VS Code).\nQuick action buttons are contextual to what is selected in the tree.\n\nPERIOD SELECTOR = application-level global context, not a per-view filter.\nSame interaction pattern as command palette. Natural language input supported.\nAffects: ledger, reports, scheduled txns, import/export — all views interpret it.\n\nBALANCE COLUMN — two modes:\n  Complete slice (account + period, no text search):\n    → Running balance. Pre-compute opening balance as of period start.\n  Filtered slice (text search active):\n    → Drop running balance. Show per-row amounts + filtered subtotal.\n  Status bar signals the mode.\n\nBOTTOM PANEL = front pocket of the binder. Global appliance only.\n  Import/export flows, reconciliation queue, scheduled transaction log.\n  Not a developer terminal for end users.\n\nSTATUS BAR = Obsidian-style. Floats near edges, only as wide as content.\n  API online/offline, balance, last reconcile date. Nothing useless in the middle.\n\nSCHEDULED TRANSACTIONS + BUDGETING = activity bar sections (separate binder sections).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
